 South Africa has a total of 34 357 confirmed Covid-19 cases according to an announcement by minister of health, Dr Zweli Mkhize, on Monday, June 1. A total of 130 of those cases have been recorded in Mpumalanga. According to data released by the Mpumalanga Department of Health, 86 recoveries have been recorded to date. There have been no deaths recorded in Mpumalanga. • Bushbuckridge: 3 cases and 1 recovery
• City of Mbombela: 23 cases and 18 recoveries
• Nkomazi: 23 cases and 21 recoveries
• Thaba Chweu: 6 cases and 2 recoveries • Chief Albert Luthuli: 2 cases and 1 recovery
• Dipaliseng: 0 cases
• Dr Pixely Ka Isaka Seme: 17 cases and 17 recoveries
• Govan Mbeki: 20 cases and 10 recoveries
• Lekwa: 7 cases and 2 recoveries
• Mkhondo: 0 cases
• Msukaligwa: 1 case and 1 recovery • Dr JS Moroka: 1 case and 1 recovery
• Emakhazeni: 2 cases and 2 recoveries
